@startuml auth-token-issue
' Requirements: L1-SEC-001, L2-SEC-002, L2-SEC-004
' Source: docs/specs/security/L1.md, docs/specs/security/L2.md
title Authentication - Bearer Token Issue (nominal and invalid credentials)
autonumber

actor "Operator" as OP
participant "HTTP API" as API
participant "Token Service" as TOK
database "IAM Store" as IAMDB
participant "Audit Logger" as AUD
database "Audit Log" as ADB

OP -> API : POST /auth/token { username, password }
activate API
note right of API
  Connection is TLS-protected in production
  (see L2-SEC-005 transport diagrams).
end note
API -> TOK : ValidateCredentials(username, password)
activate TOK
TOK -> IAMDB : FindUser(username)
activate IAMDB
IAMDB --> TOK : user record (password hash, roles) or not found
deactivate IAMDB

alt credentials valid
  TOK -> TOK : verify password hash
  TOK -> TOK : sign bearer token (subject, roles, expiry)
  TOK -> AUD : Record(event=auth-success, actor=username,\naction=token-issue, timestamp, outcome=success)
  activate AUD
  AUD -> ADB : append immutable entry
  AUD --> TOK : recorded
  deactivate AUD
  TOK --> API : TokenResponse(access_token, expires_in)
  API --> OP : 200 OK { access_token, token_type, expires_in }
else credentials invalid or user unknown
  TOK -> AUD : Record(event=auth-failure, actor=username,\naction=token-issue, timestamp, outcome=denied)
  activate AUD
  AUD -> ADB : append immutable entry
  AUD --> TOK : recorded
  deactivate AUD
  TOK --> API : CredentialValidationFailed
  API --> OP : 401 Unauthorized
end
deactivate TOK
deactivate API

note over AUD, ADB
  L2-SEC-004: authentication events are recorded with
  actor, action, timestamp, and outcome; the store is append-only.
end note
@enduml
